<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-377-590  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 377 590.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  June 26 1989 v11 n26 p14(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Topic upgrade to include Hypertext, query builder, real-timeintegration.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mace, Scott.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Verity is upgrading its Topic client-server text retrieval systemwith the addition of hypertext facilities, real-time documentintegration, a query builder and an optional bridge to StructuredQuery Language (SQL) databases.andP;  The Topic Hyperlinks feature addsautomated cross-referencing to link Topic 2.0 users directly toother documents.andP;  Topic by Example will permit users toautomatically generate text retrieval topics based on wordsselected in a model document.andP;  The Topic Real-Time System letsusers import text from such sources as news wire services.andP;  TheTopic Application Program Interface is a library of C functionsthat allow the embedment of Topic text-retrieval functions inapplications.andP;  Topic 2.0 is scheduled for Jul 1989 shipment.andP;  Forthe IBM PC, PS-2 and compatibles, the Topic Retrieval Clients are$695.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Verity Inc. (product development).andO;Product:   Topic (Data base management system) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     HypertextQuery LanguagesText Data BasesUpgrading.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>